Title: The Attack-and-Defence Group Contests
Author-Name: Subhasish M. Chowdhury
Author-X-Name-First: Subhasish M.
Author-X-Name-Last: Chowdhury
Author-Workplace-Name: University of East Anglia
Author-Name: Iryna Topolyan
Author-X-Name-First: Iryna
Author-X-Name-Last: Topolyan
Author-Workplace-Name: Mississippi State University
Abstract: This study analyzes a group contest in which one group (defenders) follows a weakest link
whereas the other group (attackers) follows a best-shot impact function. We fully
characterize the equilibria and show that with symmetric valuation the equilibrium is unique up
to the permutation of the identity of the active player in the attacker group. With asymmetric
valuation it is always an equilibrium for one of the highest valuation players to be active; it may
also be the case that the highest valuation players in group 1 free-ride completely on a player
with a lower valuation. However, in any equilibrium, only one player in the attacker group is
active, whereas all the players in the defender group are active and exert the same effort. We also
characterize equilibria for the case in which one group follows either a best-shot or a weakestlink
but the other group follows a perfectly substitute impact function.
